# numpy arrays support a wide range of operations, including element-wise arithmetic, broadcasting, and aggregation functions. Here are some common array operations:
# 1. Element-wise arithmetic: You can perform arithmetic operations on numpy arrays element-wise. 
# For example, you can add, subtract, multiply, or divide two arrays of the same shape.
# 2. Broadcasting: Numpy supports broadcasting, which allows you to perform operations on arrays of different shapes.
# 3. Aggregation functions: Numpy provides various aggregation functions, such as sum, mean, median, min, max, etc., that can be applied to arrays to compute summary statistics